menu "Anemometer Driver"

config ANEMOMETER
	tristate "Anemometer wind sensor driver"
	depends on GPIOLIB
	help
	  This driver supports generic anemometer wind sensors connected
	  via GPIO pins. It provides sysfs and character device interfaces
	  for reading wind speed measurements.

	  The driver supports configuration through Device Tree, ConfigFS,
	  or the character device interface.

	  To compile this driver as a module, choose M here. The module
	  will be called anemometer.

config ANEMOMETER_CONFIGFS
	bool "Anemometer ConfigFS support"
	depends on ANEMOMETER
	depends on CONFIGFS_FS
	help
	  Enable ConfigFS support for the anemometer driver. This allows
	  creating anemometer sensors dynamically through the ConfigFS
	  filesystem at /sys/kernel/config/anemometer/.

	  If unsure, say N.

config ANEMOMETER_DEBUG
	bool "Anemometer debugging messages"
	depends on ANEMOMETER
	help
	  Enable debug messages for the anemometer driver. This will
	  print additional diagnostic information to the kernel log.

	  If unsure, say N.

endmenu
